{
  "texts": [
    "Outside programming, GenAI Based Learning Environments have been shown to be useful for dental students (Kavadella et al., 2024), teacher training (Lu et al., 2024), creative tasks (Urban et al., 2024), math problems (Pardos and Bhandari, 2024) etc.",
    "The only negative result we could find here comes from (Zhang et al., 2024) who found students learning using GPT had a significantly worse transfer performance compared to students who interacted with actual humans, despite the ChatGPT group showing higher levels of cognitive activity on an EEG.",
    "We note that all the studies listed here evaluate slightly different objectives, and we encourage interested readers to go through the original papers for more details.",
    "All of the studies listed above work with adult students and we found very little work involving school-aged students.",
    "Frazier et al. (2024) surveyed high school students to conclude that they prefer a customized GPT over the generic version for programming education."
  ]
}